{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":9708,"name":"","username":"sovereign313","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/da6949/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-01-19T13:56:56.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo I‚Äôm building an FPS game.  I got help recently with putting an object into the scene by attaching it to the camera.  This worked wonderfully, but I‚Äôm having trouble stopping the camera from falling through the ground.  I‚Äôve tried this two ways:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ecreate a rigidbody (and collision object) on the camera node.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ecreate a ‚ÄòmainNode‚Äô and attach the camera to the main node, and attach a rigidbody / collisionbody to the main node.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEither way, I still fall through the ground.  I use the default heightmap and terrain.xml.  Here is the relevant code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eThe Terrain\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    Node* terrainNode = scene_-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"Terrain\");\n    terrainNode-\u0026gt;SetPosition(Vector3(0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f));\n    Terrain* terrain = terrainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;Terrain\u0026gt;();\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetPatchSize(64);\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetSpacing(Vector3(2.0f, 0.5f, 2.0f)); // Spacing between vertices and vertical resolution of the height map\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetSmoothing(true);\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetHeightMap(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Image\u0026gt;(\"Textures/HeightMap.png\"));\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(\"Materials/Terrain.xml\"));\n    // The terrain consists of large triangles, which fits well for occlusion rendering, as a hill can occlude all\n    // terrain patches and other objects behind it\n    terrain-\u0026gt;SetOccluder(true);\n\n    RigidBody *body = terrainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;RigidBody\u0026gt;();\n    body-\u0026gt;SetCollisionLayer(2);\n    CollisionShape *shape = terrainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;CollisionShape\u0026gt;();\n    shape-\u0026gt;SetTerrain();\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eThe Camera/Mainnode\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    Node* mainNode = scene_-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"MainNode\");\n    mainNode-\u0026gt;SetScale(1.0f);\n\n    // Camera Stuff\n    cameraNode_ = mainNode-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"Camera\");\n    Camera* camera = cameraNode_-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;();\n    camera-\u0026gt;SetFarClip(750.0f);\n    cameraNode_-\u0026gt;SetPosition(Vector3(0.0f, 27.0f, -10.0f));\n\n    // Add Our Gun\n    Node* actorNode = cameraNode_-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"Actor\");\n    AnimatedModel *actor = actorNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;AnimatedModel\u0026gt;();\n    actor-\u0026gt;SetModel(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Model\u0026gt;(\"Models/compact_handgun.mdl\"));\n    actor-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(\"Materials/Stone.xml\"));\n    actor-\u0026gt;SetCastShadows(true);\n    actorNode-\u0026gt;SetScale(Vector3(0.0005f, 0.0005f, 0.0005f));\n    actorNode-\u0026gt;SetPosition(Vector3(0.2f, -0.1f, 0.5f));\n    actorNode-\u0026gt;SetRotation(Quaternion(5, 185, 0));\n\n    RigidBody *cambody = mainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;RigidBody\u0026gt;();\n    cambody-\u0026gt;SetUseGravity(true);\n    cambody-\u0026gt;SetCollisionLayer(2);\n    cambody-\u0026gt;SetMass(1.0f);\n\n    CollisionShape *camshape = mainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;CollisionShape\u0026gt;();\n    shape-\u0026gt;SetSphere(15.0f);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI can actually see the sphere wire frame (debug is on) in the camera, but it‚Äôs supposed to be a part of the node that the camera is actually attached to as well.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:09:29.551Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":17,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":86.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1688,"topic_slug":"arg-falling-through-ground","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[9708]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2500]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7343,"title":"Zone's AmbientColor LightMask","fancy_title":"Zone\u0026rsquo;s AmbientColor LightMask","slug":"zones-ambientcolor-lightmask","posts_count":3,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_number":3,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2022-10-27T17:25:15.253Z","last_posted_at":"2022-10-28T17:16:58.872Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2022-10-28T17:16:58.872Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":false,"unpinned":null,"visible":true,"closed":false,"archived":false,"bookmarked":null,"liked":null,"tags_descriptions":{},"like_count":1,"views":72,"category_id":10,"featured_link":null,"has_accepted_answer":true,"posters":[{"extras":"latest","description":"Original Poster, Most Recent Poster","user":{"id":1456,"username":"Jens","name":"","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/j/d2c977/{size}.png"}},{"extras":null,"description":"Frequent Poster, Accepted Answer","user":{"id":484,"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"}}]},{"id":7112,"title":"What is the proper way to add mo